title: ask for the next plan from a metaplan
pid: c163d936-18ac-4419-839d-a9b064cc523d
body: |2-
  Welcome, Claude! Please read coding-advice/ORIENTATION.org, and whatever it refers to (recursively), for orientation. Also docs/forks.org -- we're not about to implement that, but this paves the way for it.

  After that, please read TODO/full-schema/metaplan_2.org.
  That is in progress, and I would like you to plan the next part of it,
  "test the relationship matrix", at TODO/full-schema/13_test-rel-matrix.org.

  Once you have written the plan, add a glossary at the top.
  When you think you develop a shorthand which,
  while often beautiful and surely efficient, is bewildering.
  I never understand it; I need plainer language.

  Finally, end the report with a 'problems' section, where you describe anything
  incompletely specified, dangerous,
  inelegant or awkward (for future coders or future users),
  or otherwise, well, problematic.
  Mark TODO any branch of the .org tree (at any level) that needs my decision.
